cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.CE, cs.DB, cs.AI

This paper deals with predictive modeling using machine learning methods applied to electronic health records. The primary focus is on interpreting the importance of predictors in the final models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which deals with the development and application of algorithms that enable computers to learn from data. 

The paper also deals with the analysis of electronic health records, which suggests the sub-category cs.CY (Computers and Society), which deals with the social and ethical implications of computing. 

The use of statistical tests and multivariate logistic regression models suggests the sub-category cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), which deals with the development and application of computational methods in various fields. 

The analysis of feature importance and the use of permutation testing suggests the sub-category cs.DB (Databases), which deals with the storage, retrieval, and management of large datasets. 

Finally, the use of machine learning methods suggests the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which deals with the development and application of intelligent agents that can perform tasks that typically require human intelligence.
